review_blob: Tried at Samsom in Nijmegen. The roasted malt belies the fact that this is a bock bier. Now, Im not a fan of roasted flavours but this is offset by the winterberry taste so its makes for above average drinking. Is it my favorite beer as a hophead? No, of course not. However, it is a nice change from the standard ubersweet bock. Come to think of it, its also a change from the average stout with all that roasted malt in it... Technically a good hybrid beer, jus not in my taste range.
This beer is unique in both taste and character. In terms of taste, its quite refreshingly dry. Not at all sweet like other bocks. It certainly the best bock I have drunk.
A somewhat uncharacteristic IPA. The hops are there but other than that I can only taste malt and a slight trace of yeast. Nothing really wrong with it but it doesn?t excite
